use and atrocity, using a range of well-known techniques including denial, delay, diversion, and delegation to pass blame for abuse and atrocities to the lowest plausible level. Mitchell argues that, despite the conventional wisdom that accountability is a 'central feature' of democracies, it is only a rare and courageous leader who acts differently, exposing the limits of accountability in democratic societies. As democracies remain embroiled in armed conflicts, and continue to try to come to grips with past atrocities, Democracy's Blameless Leaders provides a timely analysis of why these events occur, why leaders behave as they do, and how a more accountable system might be developed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jun 2020) 0aAtrocitiesvCase studies. 0aAtrocitiesxCase studies. 0aCivilians in warxCase studiesxCrimes against. 0aCivilians in warxCrimes againstvCase studies. 0aCriminal liability (International law)vCase studies. 0aCriminal liability (International law)xCase studies. 0aDemocracyxCase studiesxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aDemocracyxMoral and ethical aspectsvCase studies. 0aGovernment accountabilityvCase studies. 0aGovernment accountabilityxCase studies. 0aPolitical leadershipxCase studiesxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aPolitical leadershipxMoral and ethical aspectsvCase studies. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political ideologies / Democracy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNYUP Backlist 2000-2013z978311070644440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814763377423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780814763377.jpg  a978-3-11-070644-4  NYUP Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  a